EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 252300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND
NW FM THE NORWEGIAN BASIN TO ICELAND WITH LOW PRESSURE
EXTENDING SE THROUGH THE ATLANTIC E NERN AND E CENTRAL
SECTIONS. BY MIDDAY FRIDAY THE RIDGE IS EXP TO EXTEND W
ACROSS CENTRAL AND NERN PARTS OF THE BRITISH ISLES AND
ACROSS THE PORTPATRICK AREA OVER AND TO THE N OF ROCKALL
AND MALIN BUT WITH A CYCLONIC FLOW PERSISTING TO THE S.
DURING SATURDAY AND SUNDAY THE RIDGE IS EXP TO MOV S INTO
SERN PARTS OF THE PORTPATRICK AREA ALLOWING FRONTAL
TROUGHS TO MOV E THROUGH NERN AREAS. NEAR GALE TO GALE
FORCE WINDS THROUGH SHANNON AND ROCKALL ON THURSDAY
EVENING WILL MOD BY THE EARLY HOURS OF FRIDAY. FURTHER
GALES ARE EXP TO SPREAD E INTO BAILEY AND SE ICELAND ON
SATURDAY EVENING BECMG CONFINED TO SE ICELAND BY SUNDAY
MORNING THEN MODERATING BY EARLY AFTERNOON
